  "text": "In the EM task, the ASD group had a significantly longer response time than the control group. This finding supports the hypothesis that high-functioning individuals with ASD have less expertise in the EM task. However, covarying for response time did not explain the reduced fusiform activation in the ASD group. Individuals with ASD have been reported to have reduced fusiform activation when processing facial stimuli [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This study supports the finding that reduced fusiform activation is associated with diagnosis.",
